"{\"uid\": \"nypost.com-2025-06-02-sports-olympic-boxer-imane-khelifs-leaked-lab-results-offer-new-evidence-about-her-biological-sex\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Newly leaked test results prove that Olympic boxer Imane Khelif does have male chromosomes - after the International Olympic Committee dismissed the claims as \\\"not legitimate\\\" and let her compete in the Paris 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 51, \"end\": 63, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 134, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif - a 26-year-old who has long maintained she is female - was found to have male XY chromosomes in a 2023 test carried out by an accredited Indian doctor, newly obtained test results leaked by 3 Wire Sports show.\", \"from\": 222, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 367, \"end\": 373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"score\": 0.9941415418632757, \"rank\": 0.002410448277413429, \"text\": \"Indian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indian_people\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Chromosome analysis reveals male karyotype,\\\" read the test results - referring to male chromosomes - which left Khelif barred from the 2023 women's World Boxing Championship in India.\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 619, \"end\": 624, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.8743487244563881, \"rank\": 0.12832676266380796, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The test was conducted before that tournament by Dr. Lal Path Labs, a New Delhi lab with accreditation from the American College of Pathologists and certification from International Organization for Standardization, documents show.\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 858, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 680, \"end\": 683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krishna\", \"score\": 0.6094960962746865, \"rank\": 0.6406995388863412, \"text\": \"Lal\", \"types\": [\"Q24229398\", \"Q178885\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krishna\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Krishna\"}, {\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"score\": 0.9999896930948146, \"rank\": 1.0283114178862763e-05, \"text\": \"New Delhi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Delhi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But despite those bona fides, the IOC dismissed the test as \\\"not legitimate\\\" and \\\"ad hoc,\\\" according to the Telegraph, and allowed Khelif to compete in the women's division at the 2024 Paris Olympic.\", \"from\": 860, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 894, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6857999396707065e-15, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Leaders of the Olympic committee went a step further and even suggested that the test could be misinformation planted by Russia - where World Boxing is based - to prevent the dominant athlete from competing on the world stage.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1287, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.897657724237833, \"rank\": 0.11360480968790194, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif went on to win gold in Paris and left the sport mired in controversy, while competitors expressed fears about facing her in the ring.\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1429, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1319, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999972452866784, \"rank\": 2.754720850600246e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Italy's Angela Carini\\u00a0said she feared for her life during an Olympic bout against Khelif that lasted just 46 seconds.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1431, \"end\": 1436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"score\": 0.909853242815776, \"rank\": 0.0984713061808814, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"score\": 0.9999962103662667, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angela Carini\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angela_Carini\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The year before Khelif's chromosomal test, Mexico's Brianda Tamara Cruz also said she had a similar experience.\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \